# GitHub Copilot as PR reviewer

Use **GitHub CLI 2.88+** and a GitHub plan that includes [Copilot code review](https://docs.github.com/copilot/using-github-copilot/code-review/using-copilot-code-review). Not supported on GitHub Enterprise Server.

## This repository

Prefer **`make pr`** from the repo root: it runs `gh pr create` with **`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`** and **`--reviewer '@copilot'`** (see the **`pull-requests`** Cursor rule and **`AGENTS.md`**). Use the commands below when not using `make pr`.

## Add Copilot when creating a PR

```bash
gh pr create --base main --head <branch> --title "..." --body "..." --reviewer @copilot
```

Use the literal **`@copilot`** reviewer login. Omitting `@` (e.g. `--reviewer copilot`) can fail with *Could not resolve user with login 'copilot'*.

## Add Copilot to an existing PR

```bash
gh pr edit <number> --add-reviewer @copilot
```

## Verify

```bash
gh pr view <number>
```

Expect a line like `reviewers: Copilot (AI) …` when the request succeeded.

## If the CLI cannot resolve Copilot

Use the PR on GitHub: request review from **Copilot** in the reviewers UI, or confirm Copilot code review is enabled for the org/repo and your account.
